nating discussions of primary scriptures, key spiritual figures, discoveries of modern science, and moments of social transformation, she offers practical ways to live our lives mindfully, ethically, and sustainably. Written for students and lay readers, the book makes the case that we can sustain our planet if we maintain our strength, increase our knowledge, and remain sensitive to the beauty and the sentience that is both within us and around us.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aClimatic changesxReligious aspects. 0aMindfulness (Psychology)xReligious aspects. 0aMindfulness (Psychology). 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Comparative Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Environment and Religion. 7aBODY, MIND & SPIRIT / Mindfulness & Meditation.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848236140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438482361423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438482361/original  a978-3-11-149169-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles